The paper focuses on object detection and segmentation in industrial scenarios, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) for image analysis and classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of multi-task learning to improve classification accuracy, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper addresses the need for rapid development and production cycles in the Factory of the Future (FoF), which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY).
